1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:01,940
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,940 --> 00:00:03,610
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,610 --> 00:00:05,080
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,950 --> 00:00:08,150
(Episode 42)

5
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:12,850
Are you saying
you knew Chloe was Jin Ju?

6
00:00:20,630 --> 00:00:21,860
I asked you if you knew.

7
00:00:30,470 --> 00:00:31,540
Be straight with me.

8
00:00:32,440 --> 00:00:34,540
When you said
you were going to marry Chloe,

9
00:00:35,940 --> 00:00:37,740
you knew.

10
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:45,320
You knew she was Jin Ju
but still said you'd marry her.

11
00:00:45,380 --> 00:00:48,090
You told me to back off
because she wasn't Jin Ju.

12
00:00:49,620 --> 00:00:52,520
You knew the whole time,
and you chose to lie to me.

13
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,270
How could you...

14
00:01:02,130 --> 00:01:03,970
How could you of all people...

15
00:01:05,070 --> 00:01:08,870
You know better than anyone
how much I've missed her!

16
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:12,640
I love her.

17
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:17,150
My feelings came first.

18
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:21,420
I fell in love with Chloe first.

19
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:25,620
To you, she's Jin Ju.
But to me, she's Chloe.

20
00:01:25,620 --> 00:01:27,130
I fell for Chloe,

21
00:01:29,490 --> 00:01:31,300
and when you love someone,
you're supposed to protect them.

22
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:34,070
- Park Hyun Jun...
- You too!

23
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:39,600
You put your feelings
and your love first, too.

24
00:01:41,570 --> 00:01:44,180
Even though you knew perfectly well
that I had feelings for Chloe,

25
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:47,850
you didn't back off.

26
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:53,450
I was just being true
to my feelings, to my love.

27
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,560
Fine.

28
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,090
Then just like you,

29
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:04,060
I'll have to protect the one I love.

30
00:02:05,530 --> 00:02:07,070
Now that I know she's Jin Ju,

31
00:02:08,130 --> 00:02:09,670
I can't lose her again.

32
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:13,640
Baek Jin Ju wants to be Chloe.

33
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:17,740
She chose me, the one
who loves her for who she is, not you.

34
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,210
She made a choice,

35
00:02:20,210 --> 00:02:21,310
but she doesn't love you.

36
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:30,820
Once I find out why Jin Ju chose you
and why she became Chloe,

37
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:34,460
I'll make things right.

38
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:37,630
You should get over her already.

39
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:41,800
Who are you to tell me
to get over her?

40
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:45,640
I'm not giving up either.

41
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:47,370
Jin Ju will definitely...

42
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:50,710
come back to me.

43
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:54,350
Do you know
how much we loved each other...

44
00:02:54,350 --> 00:02:56,280
and how much I've missed her?

45
00:02:57,780 --> 00:02:59,550
Jin Ju knows better than anyone.

46
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,900
If you care about Jin Ju at all,

47
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:15,370
just make sure
she never finds out we know.

48
00:03:33,890 --> 00:03:35,090
Something feels off.

49
00:03:36,490 --> 00:03:38,920
You met the professor
and confirmed there was an error,

50
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:40,430
but you're still uneasy?

51
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:43,930
The professor's explanation matched
what Min Jun said.

52
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:46,060
But...

53
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:50,400
I asked myself who you were.

54
00:03:51,670 --> 00:03:55,040
From now on, I won't be confused
or have any doubts.

55
00:03:55,510 --> 00:03:57,340
Because you are,
without a doubt, Chloe.

56
00:03:58,940 --> 00:04:01,750
Even though he called me Chloe,

57
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:04,480
it felt like
he still saw me as Jin Ju.

58
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,550
That look in his eyes...

59
00:04:10,590 --> 00:04:14,390
Was it disappointment
that I wasn't Jin Ju?

60
00:04:14,990 --> 00:04:18,000
Or the pain of knowing I am,
but having to hide it?

61
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,670
I'm so confused.

62
00:04:25,270 --> 00:04:26,300
Anyway,

63
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:28,940
they said the fingerprint match
was an error, right?

64
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:31,640
What reason
would the professor have to lie?

65
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:34,210
Try not to worry and get some rest.

66
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:38,650
Okay, that's right.
All right, I'm hanging up now.

67
00:04:44,590 --> 00:04:45,720
How's Jin Ju?

68
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:48,530
Does she believe
the fingerprint match was an error?

69
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:51,900
She's confused.

70
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,330
I guess
I wasn't completely convincing.

71
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:58,770
Deceiving someone is no easy task.

72
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,770
Jin Ju tried so hard,
and yet her cover was blown.

73
00:05:04,310 --> 00:05:06,140
Having to hide this from her...

74
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:07,910
doesn't feel right.

75
00:05:09,010 --> 00:05:11,080
Then why did you help me?

76
00:05:18,590 --> 00:05:19,590
In that moment,

77
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:23,390
I think I was moved
by your sincerity, Mr. Park.

78
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:29,270
If you care about Jin Ju that much,

79
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:32,100
it might be worth
giving you a chance.

80
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,610
You must have changed
in the last seven years.

81
00:05:36,370 --> 00:05:37,410
Thank you.

82
00:05:37,910 --> 00:05:40,850
I'm not so sure
you should be thanking me.

83
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:45,550
You'll have a lot to bear
from now on.

84
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:47,990
You might even end up
resenting me for this.

85
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:51,590
I can handle anything
for Jin Ju's sake.

86
00:05:54,730 --> 00:05:55,790
All right.

87
00:05:57,860 --> 00:05:59,260
This is as far as I'll go.

88
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:02,700
The rest is up to you, Mr. Park.

89
00:06:03,370 --> 00:06:06,540
Of course. From now on,
I'll be the one deceiving Jin Ju.

90
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:10,680
I'll treat her as Chloe,
so she won't feel anxious.

91
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:15,750
At the same time,
I'll find out why she became Chloe,

92
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:18,680
and how I can get
the real Jin Ju back.

93
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:21,450
I will find a way.

94
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:37,070
She made a choice,

95
00:06:38,370 --> 00:06:39,470
but she doesn't love you.

96
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:42,370
Jin Ju will definitely...

97
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:45,310
come back to me.

98
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:50,050
Do you know
how much we loved each other...

99
00:06:50,050 --> 00:06:51,950
and how much I've missed her?

100
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:55,520
Jin Ju knows better than anyone.

101
00:07:23,820 --> 00:07:24,820
Father.

102
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:28,290
Our dear Chairman Park.

103
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:32,320
You can probably do it.
Actually, no.

104
00:07:33,290 --> 00:07:34,890
You're the only one who can do it.

105
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:38,860
Let me marry Chloe.

106
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:44,200
I'll marry her right away.
Say the word.

107
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:46,470
Unbelievable.

108
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,970
Are you a mess
over some stupid marriage too?

109
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:51,510
One of you is throwing a fit
because he refuses to marry,

110
00:07:52,210 --> 00:07:54,850
and the other is throwing a fit,
begging to marry.

111
00:07:56,380 --> 00:07:58,120
Pathetic, the lot of you.

112
00:07:58,650 --> 00:08:00,620
I can't stand the sight of you.
Go upstairs, now!

113
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,620
Father...

114
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:05,860
Honestly.

115
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:07,490
Mrs. Ok!

116
00:08:07,790 --> 00:08:08,790
Yes, sir.

117
00:08:10,530 --> 00:08:13,930
Call Driver Song
and get Hyun Jun upstairs.

118
00:08:14,470 --> 00:08:16,000
Yes, sir.

119
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:20,400
Father, forget
this ridiculous competition...

120
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:22,840
and just tell me
to marry her already.

121
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:26,610
Make it clear that I'm the one...

122
00:08:27,310 --> 00:08:30,850
marrying Chloe, not Park Min Jun!

123
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:34,620
Unbelievable.
Go sleep it off, you brat.

124
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:37,220
Father.

125
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:40,160
Father!

126
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,270
Father.

127
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:51,300
Oh, no. Good grief.

128
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,140
Father, come out here.

129
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,240
Take it easy.

130
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,880
Easy. Let's get you on the bed.
Just a second.

131
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:04,650
Right here.

132
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:06,420
Goodness.

133
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:10,350
Why have you been drinking so much?

134
00:09:11,190 --> 00:09:13,320
And what's this cut on your face?

135
00:09:14,290 --> 00:09:16,830
You know alcohol is the worst thing
for an injury.

136
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:21,530
Are you that upset
the wedding might not happen?

137
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:25,100
Forget my hand.

138
00:09:28,510 --> 00:09:30,040
It's right here
that the pain is killing me.

139
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,550
I'm in so much pain,

140
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,080
and no one has a clue.

141
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:44,660
How much I love her,

142
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:49,460
or how passionate
and desperate I am.

143
00:09:49,930 --> 00:09:52,260
There's not a single person
who understands.

144
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:56,570
What do you mean, "no one?" I...

145
00:09:58,740 --> 00:10:00,270
I understand.

146
00:10:01,740 --> 00:10:02,770
I do.

147
00:10:04,140 --> 00:10:06,080
I know exactly how you feel.

148
00:10:09,110 --> 00:10:11,250
How could you possibly know
how I feel?

149
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,890
My own mother,

150
00:10:17,290 --> 00:10:18,490
my father,

151
00:10:20,730 --> 00:10:23,590
and not even someone who was like
a friend and brother to me know.

152
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,300
Even the woman I love has no idea.

153
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:45,780
Oh dear, my poor Hyun Jun.

154
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:50,550
He's truly in love.

155
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:54,760
Still...

156
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:58,160
I hope it doesn't get too painful.

157
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,970
Just watching you...

158
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:07,040
is absolutely heart-wrenching...

159
00:11:07,770 --> 00:11:09,470
for some of us.

160
00:11:19,980 --> 00:11:22,720
Oh Jung Ran visited him in lockup?

161
00:11:23,450 --> 00:11:25,690
Yes, apparently she went yesterday.

162
00:11:26,990 --> 00:11:28,030
I knew it.

163
00:11:28,990 --> 00:11:33,060
She's determined to keep digging
into my past as Kim Dan Hui.

164
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:37,970
But all he knows is
that you were adopted...

165
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:40,910
and that you had some health issues.
That's it.

166
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:47,010
He doesn't know you had a twin,
so try not to worry.

167
00:12:07,830 --> 00:12:10,430
What?
Why are you staring at me like that?

168
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:12,900
What do you mean?

169
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:16,070
I just looked over when you came in.

170
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:19,180
Don't start a fight this early.
Just sit down and eat.

171
00:12:27,690 --> 00:12:28,690
Kim Dan Hui.

172
00:12:35,490 --> 00:12:38,300
Oh my, that just slipped out.

173
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,570
Honestly.

174
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,600
Watch your mouth!

175
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:46,140
It's infuriating
just to hear that name.

176
00:12:48,340 --> 00:12:50,140
Don't be so dramatic.

177
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:54,380
The name Kim Dan Hui
just rolls off the tongue for me.

178
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:55,950
Seriously.

179
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:06,720
Oh Jung Ran is certain
that I'm Kim Dan Hui.

180
00:13:07,490 --> 00:13:11,100
She believes I erased who I was
to become Kim Myung Hui.

181
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:14,100
It's not easy...

182
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:16,670
to leave your life behind
and live as someone else.

183
00:13:17,570 --> 00:13:21,040
How sordid must her past
as Kim Dan Hui have been?

184
00:13:22,010 --> 00:13:26,810
I'm going to dig up your past
and expose everything, Kim Dan Hui.

185
00:13:27,380 --> 00:13:28,380
Just you wait.

186
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:41,890
It's about time...

187
00:13:42,630 --> 00:13:45,100
we started selling the paintings
from the gallery.

188
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:46,760
The paintings?

189
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:49,870
That's my specialty.

190
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:53,200
If this goes well,
can I move back into the main house?

191
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:56,570
You take two,

192
00:13:57,710 --> 00:13:58,880
and Myung Hui, you take two as well.

193
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:00,950
Get to work.

194
00:14:01,610 --> 00:14:03,210
You want me
to split the work with Ms. Oh?

195
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,580
Not this again.

196
00:14:05,580 --> 00:14:07,690
Are you trying to make us compete?

197
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:09,850
He's making us compete...

198
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,290
and monitor each other.

199
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:19,900
This deal needs to bring in
over 20 million dollars.

200
00:14:20,260 --> 00:14:23,300
That's too much money to entrust
to one person.

201
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:27,470
Exactly. So you must leave it
to the one who's always handled it.

202
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:29,370
This tramp doesn't know
the first thing...

203
00:14:29,370 --> 00:14:30,910
about how this works.

204
00:14:31,540 --> 00:14:32,540
True.

205
00:14:33,410 --> 00:14:37,620
Myung Hui, since you're new to this,
watch how my wife handles things,

206
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:40,820
and consult with her as you go.

207
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:42,490
Consult me, my foot.

208
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,990
How can we coordinate
if you're setting us against each other?

209
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:47,460
I'll handle my end just fine.

210
00:14:48,060 --> 00:14:49,460
You're on your own.

211
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:58,640
Good grief.

212
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:01,840
What is it?

213
00:15:03,410 --> 00:15:05,910
Are you unhappy
about splitting the work?

214
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:07,880
Yes.

215
00:15:08,210 --> 00:15:10,650
It feels like you
still don't trust me.

216
00:15:14,290 --> 00:15:17,120
I'm telling you, it's too much money
to entrust to one person.

217
00:15:18,090 --> 00:15:20,320
If you do a good job on this,

218
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:22,060
then next time,

219
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:24,900
I'll trust you with the whole thing.

220
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,830
So just give it a shot.

221
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:33,170
No.
You will never be able to trust me.

222
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:36,440
Because you're the kind of person
who trusts no one.

223
00:15:45,620 --> 00:15:48,620
Oh Jung Ran is hell-bent
on digging up your past.

224
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:53,620
And Park Tae Ho has you competing
under his watchful eye.

225
00:15:54,860 --> 00:15:57,530
You have no one on your side
and enemies everywhere.

226
00:15:58,560 --> 00:16:01,070
What do you mean she has no one?
She has me.

227
00:16:02,470 --> 00:16:05,240
Don't worry about a thing, Dan Hui.
I'm here for you.

228
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:07,100
I know.

229
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:10,110
I'm always so grateful
to you and Yoon Jung.

230
00:16:11,140 --> 00:16:13,940
Don't be silly.
That's what friends are for.

231
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:18,220
I'll keep an eye on Park Tae Ho,
so don't worry.

232
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:22,290
Aren't you supposed to be tailing
Oh Jung Ran and Mr. Song?

233
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:25,120
Relax. I've got someone on them,

234
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:27,120
and I'll follow up myself
after work.

235
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:39,870
My wife was at the police station?

236
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:43,870
Yes, sir. She still seems determined
to find Kim Dan Hui.

237
00:16:45,540 --> 00:16:47,440
Just as I feared.

238
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:49,950
To think she'd fall
for that con artist's nonsense.

239
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:53,050
Just keep an eye on her for now.

240
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:57,290
I gave her work at the gallery,

241
00:16:57,290 --> 00:16:59,360
so she'll be too busy
to get distracted.

242
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:02,830
They'll either be desperate
to outdo each other...

243
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:05,060
or be busy monitoring each other...

244
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,500
so they can tear each other apart.

245
00:17:07,870 --> 00:17:09,270
Right, sir.

246
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:10,630
That aside,

247
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,640
why haven't I heard anything
about Ms. Choi?

248
00:17:15,010 --> 00:17:18,940
Have you found a way
to get that recording back yet?

249
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:21,250
I haven't found
a suitable method yet.

250
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,680
- I'm sorry, sir.
- Darn it.

251
00:17:25,320 --> 00:17:26,720
That Producer Shin or whatever.

252
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:28,950
Bring him in.

253
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:30,150
Yes, sir.

254
00:17:35,690 --> 00:17:37,530
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

255
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:41,370
This is Chairman Park Tae Ho
of the Adele Group.

256
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:44,900
It's an honor to meet you, sir.

257
00:17:46,570 --> 00:17:47,570
Right.

258
00:17:47,870 --> 00:17:50,010
I asked you here to find out...

259
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:52,910
how the competition is going.

260
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,480
In that case,

261
00:17:55,050 --> 00:17:57,150
may I speak frankly, sir?

262
00:17:57,250 --> 00:18:00,420
Of course. Please, speak your mind.

263
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:13,160
What is this?

264
00:18:13,730 --> 00:18:16,300
It's what Choi Yu Na brought me
as a bribe.

265
00:18:16,730 --> 00:18:19,070
As far as I know, it's a watch
made from a stolen design.

266
00:18:19,370 --> 00:18:21,000
A stolen design?

267
00:18:31,450 --> 00:18:33,150
Frankly, I'm deeply offended.

268
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,490
The one who invaded my privacy
to blackmail me...

269
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:38,390
tried to bribe me with a watch
made from a stolen design,

270
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:40,620
and even proposed
an inflated production budget.

271
00:18:41,430 --> 00:18:45,530
I distrust not just Ms. Choi,
but Adele itself.

272
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:48,630
I'm not interested...

273
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,300
in working with your company
in any capacity, sir.

274
00:18:58,510 --> 00:19:00,310
Producer Shin,

275
00:19:00,380 --> 00:19:03,750
you must be quite upset
about this ordeal.

276
00:19:03,910 --> 00:19:06,220
However, distrusting
the entire Adele brand...

277
00:19:07,050 --> 00:19:08,650
is a bit of an overreaction.

278
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:13,320
How about we do this?

279
00:19:17,190 --> 00:19:19,230
Producer Shin feels...

280
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:22,570
that evaluating the proposals
isn't enough.

281
00:19:24,070 --> 00:19:26,600
I've decided to add another mission
to the competition.

282
00:19:27,770 --> 00:19:29,040
Another mission?

283
00:19:30,810 --> 00:19:31,810
I refuse.

284
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:35,750
I've already created two proposals.
What more do you want from me?

285
00:19:37,150 --> 00:19:38,950
You can't just spring this on us.

286
00:19:39,020 --> 00:19:42,520
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

287
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:47,320
You recognize this, don't you?

288
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:53,260
This item was made
using a stolen design,

289
00:19:54,230 --> 00:19:55,730
and you gave it to him as a bribe.

290
00:19:56,930 --> 00:19:57,940
That's not true.

291
00:19:58,870 --> 00:20:01,770
This is the design I submitted
that won an award.

292
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:05,310
Not according
to Director Park Min Jun.

293
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:08,880
There must be
some misunderstanding...

294
00:20:08,950 --> 00:20:11,350
If it's a misunderstanding,
then prove it with your talent.

295
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:18,660
I managed to convince him
to set aside his doubts about you,

296
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:20,090
so if you don't want to do it,

297
00:20:21,890 --> 00:20:23,490
you can drop out.

298
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:28,630
So, what is the additional mission?

299
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:31,300
It's about the water you gave me.

300
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,040
A single glass of water.

301
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:36,740
Find the purest water in the world
and bring it to me.

302
00:20:37,940 --> 00:20:39,580
I'll review your submissions
in three days.

303
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:01,570
It was you, wasn't it? You did this.

304
00:21:03,670 --> 00:21:05,300
What are you talking about?

305
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:07,370
You're the one
who gave me that watch.

306
00:21:07,670 --> 00:21:10,440
You wanted me on bad terms
with Producer Shin.

307
00:21:10,910 --> 00:21:12,110
It was me.

308
00:21:17,410 --> 00:21:19,220
I'm guessing
this is about the watch.

309
00:21:21,890 --> 00:21:24,860
It was me, so leave her out of this.

310
00:21:26,190 --> 00:21:27,320
Min Jun.

311
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:30,890
I saw the watch at a budget meeting
for the production.

312
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:35,400
You bribed him with a watch
based on a stolen design.

313
00:21:38,070 --> 00:21:40,070
Come on,
how could I just let that slide?

314
00:21:41,340 --> 00:21:44,010
Jin Ju's watch design
wasn't just any design.

315
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:47,480
It represented a memory we shared
and a promise between us.

316
00:21:49,410 --> 00:21:51,420
It was bad enough
that you stole it from her,

317
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:54,080
but I couldn't just stand by
and let you use it.

318
00:21:58,660 --> 00:22:00,120
Did you really have to...

319
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:02,760
trample all over my pride?

320
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:07,460
Just like you're desperately
clinging to your past, Baek Jin Ju,

321
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,470
I'm fighting...

322
00:22:09,970 --> 00:22:12,300
just as desperately
for a future with you,

323
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:14,040
it's almost pathetic.

324
00:22:18,010 --> 00:22:19,510
Because I love you...

325
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:21,880
and because I want you,

326
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,680
I'm trying to do whatever it takes.

327
00:22:26,650 --> 00:22:29,190
So why do you always have to stomp
on my heart?

328
00:22:30,550 --> 00:22:32,790
Why can't you just be on my side,
for once?

329
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:42,070
Love isn't about owning someone,

330
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:43,930
it's about being with them.

331
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:46,470
It's not about always
getting your way just to keep them.

332
00:22:47,340 --> 00:22:49,870
It's about giving up everything
to protect them.

333
00:22:50,210 --> 00:22:51,370
That's what love is.

334
00:22:54,910 --> 00:22:56,110
What you're feeling...

335
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,950
isn't love.

336
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:00,950
It's just greed and selfishness.

337
00:23:08,190 --> 00:23:09,190
No.

338
00:23:10,390 --> 00:23:13,060
Love is, by its nature,
greedy and selfish.

339
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:16,100
The greedier you are,
the stronger it gets,

340
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:18,440
and the more selfish you are,
the more intense it becomes.

341
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:22,470
That's why, in the end,

342
00:23:24,940 --> 00:23:26,510
my love will win you over.

343
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:03,950
So the extra mission is to bring
the purest water in the world?

344
00:24:04,650 --> 00:24:07,380
I think it was the chairman's idea.

345
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:12,390
Makes sense. It seems he's giving
Choi Yu Na another chance.

346
00:24:12,990 --> 00:24:14,360
That could be it.

347
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:20,830
Chairman Park is giving Choi Yu Na
another chance?

348
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:25,570
But I thought we were dropping her.
Why?

349
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:28,040
What's he planning?

350
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:34,340
What's going through your mind?

351
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:37,280
As Chloe, not Jin Ju,

352
00:24:38,550 --> 00:24:40,020
what are you trying to accomplish?

353
00:24:45,620 --> 00:24:48,260
What if I offered to help
with the additional mission?

354
00:24:49,060 --> 00:24:50,060
That's okay.

355
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:52,300
I can handle it on my own.

356
00:24:54,030 --> 00:24:55,470
I figured you'd say that.

357
00:24:57,030 --> 00:25:00,600
But if you do need my help,
please let me know.

358
00:25:02,210 --> 00:25:03,570
I'll get going, then.

359
00:25:04,070 --> 00:25:05,080
Okay.

360
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:26,360
He's still acting strange.

361
00:25:28,130 --> 00:25:30,030
Does he want to see me as Jin Ju,

362
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:33,570
or does he actually see me
as Jin Ju?

363
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:56,330
What are you doing? Let go of me.

364
00:25:58,560 --> 00:26:01,670
What's gotten into you?
Did something happen?

365
00:26:01,870 --> 00:26:03,500
What were you and Min Jun
talking about?

366
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:06,500
Nothing much.

367
00:26:06,740 --> 00:26:08,970
- The extra mission...
- Park Min Jun.

368
00:26:10,870 --> 00:26:13,280
If that jerk asks if you love me,
what are you going to say?

369
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:18,580
- This again?
- Just answer me!

370
00:26:19,750 --> 00:26:21,790
Say you want Park Hyun Jun,
that you love him,

371
00:26:21,790 --> 00:26:23,450
and that you'll marry him.

372
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:24,790
That's what you'll say.

373
00:26:26,490 --> 00:26:28,760
Promise me you'll say that,
no matter what.

374
00:26:29,490 --> 00:26:32,300
- Did something happen?
- Just promise me first!

375
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:34,130
Why are you being like this
all of a sudden?

376
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,200
What do you think you're doing?

377
00:26:41,810 --> 00:26:42,810
What's wrong?

378
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:45,580
Can't I even kiss my own fiancee?

379
00:26:47,010 --> 00:26:48,180
You said you'd try.

380
00:26:48,180 --> 00:26:50,510
You said you'd try to love me!

381
00:26:51,210 --> 00:26:52,420
If you can't give me your heart,

382
00:26:52,420 --> 00:26:54,780
then at least lie
and say you love me.

383
00:26:55,650 --> 00:26:58,760
If you can't even lie,
then at least give yourself to me...

384
00:27:03,690 --> 00:27:05,430
Is that what you want from me?

385
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,000
No...

386
00:27:11,370 --> 00:27:12,370
I just...

387
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:16,510
Fine.

388
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:19,480
I guess that's really the only thing
I can give you.

389
00:27:21,950 --> 00:27:22,950
How about it?

390
00:27:23,650 --> 00:27:25,080
Should I undress for you right here?

391
00:27:30,250 --> 00:27:33,160
Or would you rather go
somewhere else?

392
00:27:36,660 --> 00:27:37,660
Did you...

393
00:27:40,830 --> 00:27:42,370
have to put it like that?

394
00:27:46,340 --> 00:27:47,700
You could've...

395
00:27:49,740 --> 00:27:52,510
given me a chance to apologize.

396
00:27:56,780 --> 00:27:58,580
By pushing me
into a corner like that,

397
00:28:01,050 --> 00:28:03,290
did you really have to make me out
to be that kind of guy?

398
00:29:21,260 --> 00:29:23,800
Kim Dan Hui.
Did you find anything on her?

399
00:29:24,070 --> 00:29:25,240
Do you...

400
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:28,400
have any idea
how exhausting this day has been?

401
00:29:30,170 --> 00:29:34,010
I hired someone to find out
where her adoptive parents lived,

402
00:29:34,140 --> 00:29:36,480
and then I searched
the university hospitals nearby.

403
00:29:38,250 --> 00:29:41,050
Trying to dig up information
with nothing but her name and age?

404
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:43,920
I can't tell you how much money
I had to throw around.

405
00:29:44,420 --> 00:29:47,190
Good work.
I don't care how much it costs.

406
00:29:47,890 --> 00:29:50,290
Are you saying you found something?

407
00:29:53,930 --> 00:29:57,430
Come on, I said we should
just go tomorrow morning.

408
00:29:58,200 --> 00:29:59,640
But you said there are records.

409
00:30:00,040 --> 00:30:01,140
I'm too curious to sleep.

410
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:04,740
It's better to go to the hospital
when it's empty, not crowded.

411
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:08,210
Just hurry up and drive. Now.

412
00:30:10,480 --> 00:30:12,020
This is taking years off my life.

413
00:30:21,490 --> 00:30:23,760
Records? From a hospital?

414
00:30:29,670 --> 00:30:34,170
(Dongwoo University Hospital)

415
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:42,150
Is this...

416
00:30:42,810 --> 00:30:44,750
where Kim Dan Hui was treated?

417
00:30:45,150 --> 00:30:46,380
That's what I said.

418
00:30:47,380 --> 00:30:48,550
Follow me this way.

419
00:30:57,690 --> 00:30:59,130
Darn, Yoon Jung. What do I do?

420
00:30:59,660 --> 00:31:02,170
The chairman's wife found
the hospital Dan Hui went to.

421
00:31:02,330 --> 00:31:03,330
(Administration Office)

422
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,640
We've got a huge problem.

423
00:31:10,410 --> 00:31:11,910
I just heard from Woo Jin...

424
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:14,810
that Oh Jung Ran found the hospital
where you were treated.

425
00:31:16,010 --> 00:31:19,020
She's at the hospital now
looking for Kim Dan Hui's records.

426
00:31:29,190 --> 00:31:32,560
Are you the one who found
Kim Dan Hui's medical records?

427
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:35,770
I'm not really supposed
to do this, but...

428
00:31:35,830 --> 00:31:37,470
I don't need to hear all that.

429
00:31:38,870 --> 00:31:41,570
Are you sure it's for Kim Dan Hui,
born in 1973?

430
00:31:42,270 --> 00:31:43,270
Yes.

431
00:31:44,140 --> 00:31:45,580
It's a 30-year-old record,

432
00:31:46,110 --> 00:31:48,440
so it's well past
its retention period,

433
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,950
but her surgeon used...

434
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:52,250
the surgical data
for a research paper,

435
00:31:52,250 --> 00:31:53,750
which is why
a partial record survived.

436
00:31:54,550 --> 00:31:56,450
I'm telling you, these were
extremely difficult to get.

437
00:31:57,890 --> 00:31:59,920
I heard you were paid a lot for it.

438
00:32:01,390 --> 00:32:02,390
Give me a break.

439
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:09,800
So Kim Dan Hui really did exist.

440
00:32:47,100 --> 00:32:50,070
(Pearl in Red)

441
00:32:50,570 --> 00:32:53,680
Bring me definitive proof
that Kim Dan Hui is actually dead.

442
00:32:53,810 --> 00:32:58,380
I don't get it.
Why are you so obsessed with her?

443
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,650
Like I said, it's a gut feeling.

444
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:01,350
Oh, the ultrapure water?

445
00:33:01,350 --> 00:33:04,020
It'll be ready tomorrow at 6 p.m.

446
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:05,520
Tomorrow at 6 p.m.?

447
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:09,090
Help me beat Chloe
in the extra mission.

448
00:33:09,230 --> 00:33:10,960
So what kind of help do you need?

449
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:12,330
Jung Ran, please!

450
00:33:14,260 --> 00:33:16,270
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
